main event: Two objects were observed in the sky over Pickstown, South Dakota, on July 22, 1964.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2 hours,The objects appeared as bright lights in the sky,One witness described the movement as straight line over the horizon,Major De Morse suggested that the objects could have been satellites due to their speed,There were no photographs or physical evidence documented.
sighted object: two unknown objects resembling bright lights
witness description: Major De Morse, commander of the 695 Radar Squadron
